    public class RangeSet
extends java.util.TreeSet<RangeObject>
    Extends TreeSet to provide an ordered set of RangeObjects. This does not override any methods but provides additional methods to incorporate new RangeObjects into the set without overlap.

      • addRange

        public boolean addRange(RangeObject rangeObject)
        to be used in place of add when adding RangeObjects to RangeSet. This method calls the methods to iterate over the set of existing RangeObjects to look for possible overlap, return a RangeSet of overlapping objects, remove these objects from the set, merge the new RangeObject with the set of overlapping RangeObjects and finally add the new merged object back into the set.
        Parameters:
        rangeObject - the RangeObject to be added to the set
        Returns:
        a boolean corresponding to successful addition of the new RangeObject
